### MoodTrackerPlus API Test File
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:7071/api

### Create a mood entry
POST {{baseUrl}}/moods
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "moodValue": 5,
  "notes": "Feeling great today!"
}

### Create another mood entry with specific date
POST {{baseUrl}}/moods
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "moodValue": 3,
  "notes": "A bit anxious",
  "date": "2025-11-12T10:00:00Z"
}

### List all mood entries
GET {{baseUrl}}/moods

### List mood entries with date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/moods?from=2025-11-01&to=2025-11-30

### Get mood statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/moods/stats

### Get mood statistics with date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/moods/stats?from=2025-11-01&to=2025-11-30

### Delete a mood entry (replace with actual partitionKey and rowKey)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/moods/anon/your-row-key-here

### Test validation - Invalid mood value (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/moods
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "moodValue": 10,
  "notes": "Invalid mood value"
}

### Test validation - Missing mood value (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/moods
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "No mood value"
}
